     <div type="authors_note">
   <p>
      <hi>The second volume of the Memoriall of a Chri<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>stian life I haue already translated, and am pre<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>paring it towards the Print: which conteineth the three last treatises promi<gap reason="illegible" resp="#keyers" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>ed in the Authors Prologue, to wit:</hi>
      <list>
         <item>Of Vocall Prayer.</item>
         <item>Of Mentall Prayer: wherein is treated of the life of our Sauiour Christ.</item>
         <item>Of the Loue of God wherein consisteth the perfecti<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>on of the Christian life: And therein is also trea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ted of such things as doe eyther help or hinder the same.</item>
      </list>
   </p>
   <trailer>FINIS.</trailer>
